  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What's the best applicant tracking system for a small staffing agency?",
  "response": "Choosing the best applicant tracking system (ATS) for a small staffing agency depends on your specific needs, budget, and the features you prioritize. Here are some popular ATS options that are well-suited for small staffing agencies, along with their key features:\n\n1. **BambooHR**: \n   - Great for small to midsize businesses.\n   - User-friendly interface.\n   - Offers applicant tracking, onboarding, and performance management.\n   - Customizable reporting and analytics.\n\n2. **Workable**: \n   - Easy-to-use platform with a strong focus on collaboration.\n   - Job advertising to multiple boards in one click.\n   - Robust sourcing tools and candidate evaluation features.\n   - Excellent mobile app for on-the-go recruiting.\n\n3. **SmartRecruiters**: \n   - Focuses on collaboration and provides an intuitive platform.\n   - Offers free and paid job postings to various job boards.\n   - Strong candidate management and communication tools.\n   - Comprehensive hiring analytics.\n\n4. **Zoho Recruit**: \n   - Cost-effective with a suite of features tailored for staffing agencies.\n   - Great for managing candidates, job openings, and client relationships.\n   - Mobile-friendly with customizable workflows.\n   - Good integration with other Zoho products and third-party apps.\n\n5. **Bullhorn**: \n   - Designed specifically for staffing agencies.\n   - CRM functionality integrated with ATS features.\n   - Excellent for managing candidate data and client relationships.\n   - Customizable workflows and reporting capabilities.\n\n6. **Jobvite**: \n   - Comprehensive hiring solution with social recruiting features.\n   - Strong focus on candidate engagement.\n   - Offers analytics to improve hiring strategies.\n   - Good for both small and larger organizations.\n\n7. **iCIMS**:\n   - Robust features for applicant tracking and onboarding.\n   - User-friendly interface and significant customization options.\n   - Provides strong analytics and reporting capabilities.\n   - More scalable, making it suitable if you plan to grow.\n\n### Considerations for Choosing an ATS:\n- **Budget**: Determine how much you're willing to spend, as pricing can vary widely among ATS providers.\n- **Features**: Identify the features that are most important to your agency, such as candidate sourcing, mobile access, reporting, and integrations with other tools.\n- **Ease of Use**: An intuitive system will save you time and reduce training needs.\n- **Customer Support**: Good customer service can be essential, especially if you encounter issues or have questions.\n- **Scalability**: Consider if the ATS can grow with your business as your staffing agency expands.\n\nIt's recommended to take advantage of free trials or demos offered by these platforms to see which one aligns best with your agency's workflow and preferences.",
